==English==

===Noun===
# (''broadcasting'') The [[time]] of day when a [[radio]] or [[television]] station begins [[broadcasting]], usually after being off the air for several hours.
#: '''''Sign on'' for the radio station is at 5 a.m.''

===Verb===
'''to [[sign]] [[on]]'''

# To join something, after signing
# (''broadcasting'') To begin broadcasting a radio or television signal, usually at the beginning of a broadcasting day and after being off the air for several hours.
#: ''Years ago, the TV station would '''sign on''' at 5 a.m., but now it broadcasts 24 hours a day.''
#{{idiom}} To [[log on]]; to start using a [[computer]], [[radio]], etc., or to start [[talking]].
# To sign on for the [[dole]]